{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "As a second baseline, we employ a 3D-systolic array (3D-TPU) architecture based on the Google TPU-v4 [18].",
    "The 3D-TPU architecture is a fourtier system featuring 128x128 systolic array connected via a 3D-torus interconnect [18].",
    "Each tier contains 4 cores placed in a 2 x 2 configuration, maintaining comparable tier area to that of Atleus.",
    "Additionally, we utilize the same clock frequency and the amount of on-chip SRAM to align with Atleus's systolic array configuration for fair evaluation.",
    "We also consider a Nvidia Tesla V100 GPU for comparative performance evaluation."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
